y of the transition region, $\\partial\n\\mathcal{T}_h$, is a cylinder, while in dissipative systems, $\\partial\n\\mathcal{T}_h$ is an ellipsoid.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Wed, 24 Jul 2019 21:21:03 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Thu, 3 Oct 2019 15:49:14 GMT"}],"update_date":"2019-11-05"}
